args:
After a mysterious voice rings out in Notte's
mind, she is flooded with information and faints.
When she comes to, she has grown to the size
of a human and recalls the exact way to the
Faerie Kingdom! Hoping to discover what's
behind this, the party hurries on their way.
(I have something I must convey to you.\nAccept it.)
Okay, what the hey are you talking...\nWait, huh? What's going on?!
Things are running through my head...\nNo! No, stop!
I'm Zethia! I live in this castle.\nWhat's your name?
Hee hee! That's a really nice name.\nIt's a pleasure to meet you, Notte.
Now come with me and I'll introduce you\nto my big brother.
Yeah! You don't have to be scared;\nhe's really nice.
Yes, I see. The child may be able to\nendure the weight of this role yet.
While I loathe the thought of placing such\nfuture hardship upon the shoulders of a\nbabe, I am left with no other choice.
Nnngh... My head...feels like it's about\nto crack open like a melon...
Huh? Oh hey, guys! I think I just\npassed out there for a sec.
Whatever happened to you, Notte?\nWhy do you...look like that?
My body feels weird...\nAnd my hands and feet, too...
Okay, what the hey is going on here?\nHow is this even POSSIBLE?!
Uh, you ARE Notte, right?\nNotte the faerie?
Yep! I'm her in the flesh!\nEr, but with a lot more flesh than usual.
This doesn't seem to be another one'a\nthem weird illusions...
How came you to be in this form, Notte?
Look, first things first: Are you all right?\nYou were screaming about your head\njust a few moments ago.
Huh? Oh yeah, the ol' noggin's fine.\nAnd that dumb voice is gone, too.\nOther than being all ginormo, I feel great.
It's something of a shock, I must say.\nI can't quite believe I've finally seen\nsuch a thing with my own eyes.
Do you know something about this,\nChelle?
I've read some old tomes that tell of\nfaeries growing during adolescence.
Though I never thought to witness\nthe actual event for myself.
This is beyond anything I might have\nexpected—and with Notte, no less!
Then you believe Notte has...er,\nembiggened because she has finally\nreached her adolescence?
Man, this seems like a LOT.\nI was just hoping for a zit or something...
If we follow this path, we'll see a big tree,\nthen a narrower path we can follow...
Wait, so you know where we are now?
Okay, everybody just slow your rolls.\nNotte was stumblin' around as lost as\nthe rest of us just a second ago!
Did she not say she had never set foot\nbeyond South Grastaea before?
I haven't! I've never been to this place\nin my entire LIFE!
But somehow I still remember it.\nThe woods, the mountain... All of it.
You claimed to be hearing a voice\ninside your head earlier, yes?
The thing was all, ＂accept it＂ or something,\nand then everything went all woobly.

I can't claim to have a perfect handle
on the situation, but it may be that the
Faerie Kingdom has sent us information
using Notte as a conduit.
As we have seen firsthand, the faeries\ncommand a variety of different powers;\nsuch would be well within their abilities.
So the magic they used to communicate\nwith us also caused Notte to grow?

That is my guess at the moment—and if
that is the case, there is no way to revert
her growth save for completing our journey
to the Faerie Kingdom.
Are you okay to travel, Notte?
I think so? I mean, my mind is fine—\nand yeah, this body is SUPER weird,\nbut it seems to work all right.
We'll make for the peak of the mountain.\nSheila and Notte, if you two would be so\nkind as to lead the way?
